<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR PTO HOUSING ASSEMBLY REMOVAL (IF EQUIPPED) - FLYWHEEL INSTALLATION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>FLYWHEEL INSTALLATION</title>
        <para>Install the flywheel as follows: (
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600754">7.54</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            )
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install flywheel over dowel guide pins and secure to crankshaft with ten (10) flywheel
                mounting bolts.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="underscr">FOR APPLICATIONS USING AUTOMATIC TRANSMISSIONS</emph>, INSTALL SPACER,
                        FLEXPLATE(S) AND REINFORCING RING, THEN INSTALL THE TEN (10) FLYWHEEL MOUNTING BOLTS.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two (2) dowel guide pins and install remaining two (2) mounting bolts. Tighten all
                twelve (12) flywheel mounting bolts to the special torque value.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600753" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg7232" filename="../figeg7/EG7232.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.53 Installing PTO Rear Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600754" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5290" filename="../figeg5/EG5290.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 7.54 Installing The Flywheel</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
